title: For Sale:  True Custom Glock 22
postcontent:
I'm a mechanical engineer and I like to tinker with things. After purchasing a glock 19 for EDC I decided to have a bit of fun with my oft neglected 22. For the past four months I've been developing slide improvements, magazine wells, and magazine base pads using soildworks, edgecam, and our FEA suite to make sure everything is as robust as necessary. The result of that research and development is what I have for sale today. Despite the improvements, I still don't shoot the 22 very often and would rather have a 17. All of the design work and machining was done by me with the help of a few other engineers and a 40 year veteran machinist. The actual work was done on a Fadal CNC machine with carbide tools and liquid coolant. The Cerakote was applied by the gentlemen at Johnson Customs in Springfield and they did an exceptional job. They are a factory trained and certified Cerakote dealer and do thousands of parts for large operations. The stippling is comfortable for hours of shooting as it is a relatively low profile pattern. The area around the mag release has been scalloped to facilitate depressing the release. If you have any other questions about the build or the firearm itself, please feel free to ask. If you don't want this gun but have a glock you would like modified in a similar fashion, feel free to contact me. I have a full suite of other designs including windows, other serration patterns, RMR cuts, etc. The magazine well in the photos is a 3D printed prototype that I am working on. The aircraft grade aluminum production version will be ready to go in the coming days and that will be included with the pistol. The magazine base pads are further away from completion so they will not come with this gun.Pistol comes with 6 factory 15 round glock mags. 
The streamlight is not included in this sale. This wonderful pistol is going for $1250. Thanks,Casey
